metadata.name: The Sprawl #24
metadata.description:
The sprawl. A shimmering maze of light and beauty. A living, breathing, churning mess thrown into chaos by a long forgotten runtime exception. Automaton ghosts operate on hard-coded rulesets, grasping to understand the zero-player game in which they are trapped. Individuals are lost to the great invisible broken machine as exponential memory leaks spin out endless reconfigurations, expanding and expanding for a momentary glimpse at a fraction of reality.

@d0n.xyz

metadata.name: Foundations #214
metadata.description:
In march of this year, I started working on a new series involving multi-layering, and overriding shapes. Drawing and playing with colors and opacity.
It started with squares and grid, it then involved deformations, and circles and other experimentations.
This path fits with my artistic generative approach: rather than having a completely predefined idea, I start with a simple concept that evolves during creation. Then surprises happened, and I embraced them.

But this year was not like any other: 2022 has gifted me with a new birthday, the one of my son.

Over the past twelve months, I’ve watched him discovering the world surrounding him, learning and trying new things, laughing, or getting frustrated, sad or happy…
While learning to become a parent, I’ve been in an introspection phase where I questioned what it means to be “a father”. What impact will I have on my son, consciously or not?

“Foundations” takes shape in this context: 2 humans trying and exploring while being inspired by each other.
This series is a first of a set of at least 3, that illustrates an idea of what is an “Identity”, and what makes us who we are.

The foundations of an identity are laid in the first days of a child’s life. They will be influenced by many factors; including parenting, cultural environment, life experiences… 
Of course, as humans we are in constant evolution; life happens, sometimes for the best, sometimes for the worst, and our personality will be impacted…
But this will be a topic for another time. 


Today, we are at the start.

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #4
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden “template” canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‘template’ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Infinite Scaling System #71
metadata.description:
This generative system has a beginning, but no ending. It scales infinitely in different directions as unlimited shapes are added. Special care was taken to avoid memory overflows, impossibly big numbers, and poor performance. 

Rendered using P5.JS

metadata.name: Impressions of Order #137
metadata.description:
‘Impressions of Order’ is a collection of 300 generative compositions. 

Inspired by 90s ROM cartridges, server farms and future cityscapes this project explores perception and documentation of ‘order’ within complex systems. 

--------------------------------------------------------

This artwork is best enjoyed in high-resolution so that the subtle layering, colour shifts, variation in hard and soft edges, faint impressions of construction, and the various low-probability glitchy events can be fully appreciated. 

By default, the artwork will load in 2K resolution (1400 x 2000 px). It is recommended that you view the work in 4K or 6K to appreciate the finer details. 

The keyboard buttons: “2”, “4”, and “6” can be pressed to change the resolution to 2K, 4K and 6K resolution accordingly. 

To download an image at its current resolution, press the keyboard button “S”.

--------------------------------------------------------

Artwork created with p5.js

@nbswwit
Sept 2022

metadata.name: Towards the light #109
metadata.description:
A strong light projects on the eyes
Dark matter
Multi-pixel presence and Simultaneous perception
The unknown world can only be perceived as fuzzy
In sight
Focus, reflect, scatter
Multiple unfocused images overlap
Color Halo is like picture frame ，can show the human form
out sight
The distance did not disappear
Through a narrow cave，there will be another mysterious unknown land

50% of secondary market royalties go to minters.

Twitter: @guooooog

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: fx(plane) #51
metadata.description:
Plane is the most basic component of three-dimensional form. Placing parallel planes to form abstract art in three-dimensional space is an intriguing concept.

-colors chosen from 23 distinct color palette

-made with P.JS(WEBGL)
